      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: pause/resume commands via optional PausableBackend (islo first)",
        "body": "## What\n\nAdds a generic, opt-in **pause/resume** capability to crabbox and implements it for the **islo** provider, which natively supports snapshot-to-disk pause + resume.\n\n## Design (right altitude, not a one-off)\n\nMirrors crabbox's existing optional-interface pattern (`DoctorBackend`, `CleanupBackend`):\n\n- **`PausableBackend`** interface (`Backend` + `Pause`/`Resume`) plus `PauseRequest`/`ResumeRequest` in `internal/cli/provider_backend.go`.\n- **`crabbox pause` / `crabbox resume`** commands that reuse `stop`'s flag parsing and provider resolution, then dispatch via a type assertion. Providers that don't implement the interface return a clear `provider=<name> does not support pause` — no behavior change for anyone else.\n- A compile-time assertion (`var _ core.PausableBackend = (*isloBackend)(nil)`) guards signature drift.\n\n## islo implementation\n\n`Pause`/`Resume` call the Islo SDK's `PauseSandbox`/`ResumeSandbox` (which return a decoded `SandboxResponse`), resolve the lease like `stop`, and **keep the lease claim across a pause** so it can be resumed.\n\n## Tests\n\n`TestIsloPauseResumeCallProvider` (backend dispatches to the provider with the resolved sandbox name; non-Crabbox ids rejected). `go build ./...`, `go vet`, `gofmt`, and the full `internal/cli` + `internal/providers/islo` suites pass.\n\n## Verified live (api.islo.dev)\n\n```\nwarmup → status: state=running ready=true\npause  → paused lease=…        → status: state=paused  ready=false\nresume → resumed lease=…       → status: state=running ready=true\n```\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)",
